SIMPLE: urge
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Urge
<hw>Urge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Urged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Urging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>urgere</ets>; akin to E. <ets>wreak</ets>. See <er>Wreak</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To press; to push; to drive; to impel; to force
onward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Through the thick deserts headlong <qex>urged</qex> his
flight.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To press the mind or will of; to ply with motives,
arguments, persuasion, or importunity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My brother never⟦br⟧
Did <qex>urge</qex> me in his act; I did inquire it.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To provoke; to exasperate.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Urge</qex> not my father's anger.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To press hard upon; to follow closely</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Heir <qex>urges</qex> heir, like wave impelling wave.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To present in an urgent manner; to press upon
attention; to insist upon; <as>as, to <ex>urge</ex> an argument; to
<ex>urge</ex> the necessity of a case.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>To treat with forcible means; to take severe or
violent measures with; <as>as, to <ex>urge</ex> an ore with intense
heat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To animate; incite; impel; instigate; stimulate;
encourage.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Urge
<hw>Urge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To press
onward or forward.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be pressing in argument; to insist; to
persist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urgence</ent>⟦br⟧
